    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-03T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taejon</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-03T23:00:00+10:00"
                            >July 3, 1950—11 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 4—4:14 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Mytel 7, July 3.<note n="1" xml:id="d213fn1">Not printed.</note> Enemy
                    thrusts through Yongen and Songjongni do not appear to have made much progress
                    today. Enemy believed to have pushed considerable number troops and equipment
                    across Han River below Seoul with air opposition seemingly light. New threat has
                    developed to east, this time in Yoju and Wonju areas which reportedly in enemy
                    hands and with enemy advancing rapidly southeast. This enemy thrust evidently
                    came from Chunchon direction and represents break through 6th division
                    defenses.</p>
                <p>Rhee arrived in Pusan yesterday by sea from Mokpo and is evincing strong desire
                    return Taejon. About 105 assemblymen have registered with Assembly secretariat
                    and others are known to have gone <pb facs="0322" n="302" xml:id="pg_302"/> to
                    constituencies in south. Cabinet had inaugurated informal meetings, though there
                    little evidence of government offices being set up in Taejon. People more calm
                    here today than any time since outbreak hostilities. Commodity prices have risen
                    somewhat Taejon where influx of refugees relatively great, but little
                    elsewhere.</p>
                <p>Department pass <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
